The World Health Organisation is deploying more than 40 experts in South Africa. JOHANNESBURG - Health Minister Dr Zweli Mkhize will officially welcome the first members of the WHO Surge Team that have arrived in South Africa to bolster the national COVID-19 response. The World Health Organisation is deploying more than 40 experts in South Africa. They landed in Johannesburg last week. The experts will offer support in various fields such as surveillance, case management, infection prevention and control at national and provincial levels. READ: World coronavirus deaths pass 750,000 - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.